    {"id":"post_1","type":"sharp_opinion","source_theme":"problem_centric_pitch","text":"Smaller VRMs don't need a prettier pitch deck. They need a sharper diagnosis than the bigger company brought to the table.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"sharpest_observation","best_timing":"early_week","publish_after_linkedin":false,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"founding_sales","source_file":"linkedin/post_1.txt","theme":"problem_centric_pitch","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_2","type":"recognition","source_theme":"door_count_vanity_metric","text":"Door count is a vanity metric if half the doors came attached to owners your system was never built to survive.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"recognition_line","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"founding_sales","source_file":"linkedin/post_2.txt","theme":"door_count_vanity_metric","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_2.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_3","type":"diagnostic","source_theme":"excavation_questions","text":"A better early question than 'what are your goals?' is 'tell me about the last time this property created a real problem for you.' Much harder to hide inside a polished answer.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"tactical_question","best_timing":"after_post_1","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"founding_sales","source_file":"linkedin/post_1.txt","theme":"excavation_questions","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_4","type":"story_detail","source_theme":"time_audit","text":"Many owners say the property takes 'a couple hours a week' until you count the guest messages, portal checks, vendor calls, and the mental overhead. Funny how that number moves.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"story_detail","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"founding_sales","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"time_audit","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
